{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"Jira reconciler silently fails to sync comments and inbound links while reporting\n`converged` — three distinct defects, all hidden behind a pass that counts failed\nsub-operations toward \"applied N of N\" and exits 0.\n\n## Context\n\nInvestigation (/rebar-debug, 2026-07-17) established that status/existence sync is\nhealthy (0 drift across ~1200 tickets), but three field-level sync paths are broken\nand invisible:\n\n- **Comment sync (P1):** `get_comments()` returns only the first 50 of N comments\n  (no `--paginate`), so outbound dedup re-posts the rest every pass. 13 tickets have\n  been inflated to Jira's 5000-comment hard cap (local truth: 22-76 comments each);\n  further adds fail `COMMENTS_PER_ISSUE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED` and are swallowed.\n- **Inbound link direction (P2):** `_diff_links_inbound` (inbound_differ.py:519-527)\n  AND `_diff_link_removals` (outbound_links.py:198-203) both invert the\n  inward/outward -> blocks/depends_on mapping. Latent since 2026-06-15 (`f6687adf4`);\n  UNMASKED when the outbound direction fix landed (`6b25dbead`/`43d154523`, 07-16/17)\n  — the two inversions previously cancelled on round-trip. Now ~815 inbound link\n  applies/pass are cycle-rejected by rebar's guard.\n- **Observability (meta):** a pass with failed sub-ops still prints `applied N of N`\n  / exits 0 / logs `converged`. The `RECONCILER_FAIL_SILENT_NOOP` flag (default off)\n  exists but is not enabled; swallowed comment failures land in `comment_errors` and\n  are never counted as failures.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] P1: outbound comment sync is idempotent — a steady-state pass emits 0 comment\n      adds for a ticket already mirrored, even when the Jira side has >50 comments.\n- [ ] P2: an inbound Jira `Blocks` link round-trips to the correct rebar relation\n      (`blocks`/`depends_on`) with NO cycle-rejection against the correct local edge,\n      in BOTH the add path and the removal path.\n- [ ] Observability: a pass with any silent sub-op no-op reports failure (non-zero\n      exit) rather than `converged`, once P1/P2 remove the standing noise.\n- [ ] Test hardening: unit + integration + E2E coverage added for all three failure\n      modes AND same-kind gaps; the new tests fail on the pre-fix code.\n- [ ] Jira data cleanup: the 13 capped tickets are de-duplicated so new comments can\n      sync again — executed AFTER P1 deploys to main, under the safety plan below.\n\n## Jira cleanup safety plan (T4 — destructive-step rollback)\n\nThe comment de-duplication is IRREVERSIBLE (Jira comment deletion cannot be undone\nvia API). It is a deliberate, justified destructive step (the tickets are permanently\nunable to sync until duplicates are purged), executed only with these guardrails:\n\n- [ ] **Pre-deletion backup:** export the FULL comment payload (id, body, author,\n      created) for all 13 tickets to a versioned JSON artifact BEFORE any deletion, so\n      any comment can be re-created if needed.\n- [ ] **Dry-run first:** the cleanup script has a `--dry-run` (default) mode that\n      lists exactly which comment IDs would be deleted and which one canonical copy of\n      each distinct body is kept; a human reviews the dry-run diff before `--execute`.\n- [ ] **Keep-one dedup rule:** for each distinct normalized body, keep the OLDEST\n      copy (lowest created) and delete the rest; never delete a body with only one copy.\n      Only delete comments authored by the bridge bot identity (never human comments).\n- [ ] **Idempotent + resumable:** re-running is safe; on partial failure, re-run\n      `--dry-run` to see the remaining duplicates and resume. Deletions are logged\n      (ticket, comment id, body hash) to an artifact as they happen.\n- [ ] **Sequencing:** run ONLY after P1 is deployed to main, else the buggy\n      reconciler re-inflates duplicates within minutes.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All child tickets (P1, P2, observability, test-hardening, Jira-cleanup) are closed.\n- [ ] A reconcile pass shows 0 comment-cap failures and 0 inbound link\n      cycle-rejections for the previously-affected tickets.\n- [ ] The cleanup backup artifact + dry-run log exist before any live deletion."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784316280131887001,"uuid":"8c377ed7-08c7-46e2-9d1d-e9c406f65ddb"}